body:
Documenting a lint ambiguity. The following will throw a Verilator ENCAPSULATED warning:

```
class Paramed #(parameter int P);
   protected int m_i;
   static function int self();
      Paramed#(1) p = new;
      p.m_i = 10;  // For Paramed#(2)'s function we're looking into a different Paramed#(1)
      return p;
   endfunction
endclass

module t;
   Paramed#(1) p1;
   Paramed#(2) p2;
endmodule
```

Although Paramed is used in the same class, the parameters are different in the class, so Verilator considers the access coming from a different class so it warns.  I was considering fixing this but did some research... It's not clear what IEEE intends here (are different parameterized classes the same base class - presume not). As at least one other major simulator warns also, sticking with current behavior.
